            <xs:element minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1" name="defaultValues" type="xs:string"
                        sawsdl:modelReference="http://iec.ch/TC57/CIM100#MetaInformation.defaultValues">
                <xs:annotation>
                    <xs:documentation>defaultValues is a energy data space specific attribute to hold relevant default
                        values. The format to use can freely be chosen based on the implementation. Most commonly you
                        would expect a semi-colon separated name value pair, like: "minPower=value; maxPower=value;
                        avgPower=value".
